article.headline: Princeton 27, Colgate 26 (OT)
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Jeff Terrell scored on a 4-yard run in overtime and Tom Methvin stopped a 2-point conversion attempt to give Princeton a 27-26 win over Colgate on Saturday. Princeton (4-0) got the ball first in overtime to take a 27-20 lead. Colgate (2-3) answered with a 26-yard touchdown reception by Jordan Scott. The Raiders opted for the win with a two point conversion, but Mike Saraceno was stopped in the backfield by Methvin. Colgate opened the scoring when Saraceno ran in a touchdown from a yard out after a Princeton fumble. The Tigers evened the score with 11:33 to play in the first half when Terrell connected with Brendan Circle for a 33-yard score. Princeton took a 10-7 lead a couple minutes later when Connor Louden made a 33-yard field goal attempt. Another 1-yard touchdown run by Scott run with 1:36 remaining gave Colgate a 13-10 halftime lead. Rob Toresco took back the lead for Princeton when he scored from a yard out late in the third quarter. The Raiders briefly regained the lead 20-17 on another Saraceno touchdown run. Connor Louden connected on a 34-yard field goal with 4:02 to play to tie the game.
